Text: Paul Pierce had 14 points, six rebounds, and eight assists, as the Boston Celtics pulled away from the Charlotte Bobcats after halftime to cruise to a 105-88 win Saturday. Jason Terry added a team-high 15 points for the shorthanded Celtics (36-290, who played without Kevin Garnett (adductor) for just the second time all season. The hosts overcame Garnett's absence to earn their 11th straight win at the TD Garden and avenge a blowout loss to the lowly Bobcats (14-52) on Tuesday.
